Parsing social sentiment data can tell a firm if it is about to have more warranty claims or recall costs due to a poorly performing product. Alternatively, this data could originate from sensors that are embedded in the manufacturerâ€™s products.
Similarly, one could scan sentiment data, recall information, litigation case filings, etc. to monitor whatâ€™s happening with competitorsâ€™ solutions. If competitors are struggling, then this could indicate a need to bump up oneâ€™s expected sales and supporting marketing numbers.
Retailers are using weather data to forecast daily sales and manage payroll costs.

Budgeting and planning is no longer a once-a-year event in many firms. As their data has become more abundant, more diverse and more instantaneous, they need to re-invent and re-imagine their budgeting and planning processes.
New tools, new data sources and a dose of additional innovation should trigger the creation of new/better planning software solutions that will definitely benefit businesses. That just may be the best outcome of Workdayâ€™s announcement.
